g.text: "An attempt will be made to find how to make machines use language,
form abstractions and concepts, solve kinds of problems now reserved
The primary goal of Computer Vision is to convert light into meaning
It emits light rays in all directions and
they bounce away in multiple directions.
Finally, some rays will hit the observer
Given the 3D scene, we want to render a 2D image of that scene
- Many 3D scenes yield the same 2D image
It relies on low level manipulation of the images
- The computer sees only pixel matrix
